The paper deals with the problem of verifying the null space condition in compressed sensing, which is a fundamental problem in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed algorithms are based on polynomial-time methods, which are often used in computational complexity theory (cs.DS) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also discusses simulation results, which may fall under the category of statistical learning (cs.SI).
